1 (b) The purpose of this act is to develop and carry into effect a state program to
2 encourage the production and purchase of sustainable aviation fuel in this State for
3 the purposes of:
4 (1) Developing the market and industry for sustainable aviation fuel in this
5 State and promoting jobs and businesses in this State in the sustainable aviation fuel
6 industry; and
7 (2) Reducing greenhouse gases emitted by domestic air carriers that
8 operate in this State, specifically emissions occurring on takeoff and landing at
9 airports in this State.
10 (c) The promotion and development of the sustainable fuel industry in this
11 State is an important public purpose which incentivizes the development of
12 business and industry in this State.
13 (d) The protection and preservation of the natural resources of this State by
14 incentivizing the purchase of sustainable aviation fuel is an important public
15 purpose which will limit the emissions of greenhouse gasses from air carriers
16 operating in this State and thus lower the contributions air travel in this State make
17 to climate change, which threatens the health, safety and welfare of the residents of
18 this State and the economy of this State.
19 (e) The provisions of this act are intended to serve an important public purpose
20 and ensure that the State receives valuable benefits and fair consideration in
21 exchange for each incentive of money from the program because:
22 (1) The program requires the dispensing agency to review all facts, figures
23 and necessary information when making each incentive of money from the program
24 to ensure the incentive meets the requirements of the program;
25 (2) The promotion and development of the sustainable fuel industry in this
26 State and the protection and preservation of the natural resources of this State are
27 important public purposes that promote job growth in this State and protect the
28 health, safety and welfare of the residents of this State; and
29 (3) The dispensing state agency may not make an incentive of money from
30 the program unless the air carrier purchases sustainable aviation fuel in accordance
31 with the requirements of the program.

